mean_cn: n.本能，天性；天分，天资；直觉
mean_en: a feeling that makes you do sth or believe that sth is true, even though it is not based on facts or reason
sentence: Even well-fed cats will kill mice because of their hunting instincts.
sentence_trans: 即使喂得很饱的猫也会捉老鼠，因为它们有捕食老鼠的天性。
word_etyma: in内 + stinct刺激 → 内在的刺激 → instinct本能
